## Add Chart Repo
```bash
helm repo add homeylab https://homeylab.github.io/helm-charts/
# update the chart, this can also be run to pull new versions of the chart for upgrades
helm repo update homeylab
```

## Prerequisites
Point unpoller at a reachable UniFi controller. Set `settings.unifi.config.url` (e.g. `https://unifi.example.org:8443`) and credentials via `settings.unifi.auth.user`/`settings.unifi.auth.pass` â€” these render into a chart-managed Secret wired via `envFrom`. Alternatively, set `existingSecret` to the name of your own Secret providing `UP_UNIFI_CONTROLLER_0_USER`/`UP_UNIFI_CONTROLLER_0_PASS` (and any InfluxDB auth keys); `existingSecret` takes precedence and the chart Secret is not rendered.

For self-hosted UniFi Network Application, the `user` field is the account's email.

InfluxDB output is optional; set `settings.influxdb.enabled: true` plus `settings.influxdb.config.*` and `settings.influxdb.auth.*` (also rendered into the same chart-managed Secret, or provide via `existingSecret`).

## Install
```bash
helm install unpoller homeylab/unpoller -n unpoller --create-namespace

# with own values file - recommended
helm install -f my-values.yaml unpoller homeylab/unpoller -n unpoller --create-namespace
```

### OCI Registry Support
```bash
helm install unpoller -n unpoller oci://registry-1.docker.io/homeylabcharts/unpoller --version X.Y.Z --create-namespace
```

### Install Example
Only some options are shown, view `values.yaml` for an exhaustive list.

<details closed>
<summary>custom-values.yaml</summary>
<br>

```yaml
# custom-values.yaml
settings:
  unifi:
    config:
      url: "https://unifi.example.org:8443"
    auth:
      user: "unpoller"
      pass: "fakepassword"

metrics:
  enabled: true
  serviceMonitor:
    enabled: true

## Alternative to ingress - Gateway API HTTPRoute (chart does NOT create the Gateway)
# httproute:
#   enabled: true
#   parentRefs:
#     - name: my-gateway
#       namespace: gateway-system
#   hostnames:
#     - unpoller.example.org
```
</details>
